comment: Lemma for ~ log2ub . The proof of ~ log2ub , which is simply the evaluation of ~ log2tlbnd for ` N = 4 ` , takes the form of the addition of five fractions and showing this is less than another fraction. We could just perform exact arithmetic on these fractions, get a large rational number, and just multiply everything to verify the claim, but as anyone who uses decimal numbers for this task knows, it is often better to pick a common denominator ` d ` (usually a large power of ` 1 0 ` ) and work with the closest approximations of the form ` n / d ` for some integer ` n ` instead. It turns out that for our purposes it is sufficient to take ` d = ( 3 ^ 7 ) x. 5 x. 7 ` , which is also nice because it shares many factors in common with the fractions in question.
